sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction

Class ParameterAbstractionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction.ParameterAbstractionManager

  • public class ParameterAbstractionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A ParameterAbstractionManager provides functionalities for generation of AbstractParameter in an AbstractModel from the informations provided by a SBML Model.
    The ParameterAbstractionManager works under the assumption that the SBML Model has been pre-processed with a ModelPreprocessingManager.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

      • ParameterAbstractionManager

        ParameterAbstractionManager(AbstractModel model,
                            org.sbml.jsbml.Model sbmlmodel)
                     throws NullAbstractModelException,
                            NullSBMLModelException
        Constructor initializes the ParameterAbstractionManager with the given AbstractModel and SBML Model.
        If one between the two inputs is null, then a proper exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        model - The AbstractModel where the informations must be stored.
        sbmlmodel - The SBML Model from which the informations are retrieved.
        Throws:
        NullAbstractModelException - When model == null.
        NullSBMLModelException - When sbmlmodel == null.

    • Method Detail

      • generateParameter

        private AbstractParameter generateParameter(org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter p)
        This method generates an AbstractParameter in the AbstractModel using the informations provided by the given SBML Parameter.
        Parameters:
        p - A SBML Parameter in the SBML Model.
        Returns:
        An AbstractParameter in the AbstractModel whose the identifier and name are equals to those of p.

      • computeParameterUnit

        private void computeParameterUnit(org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter p,
                                  AbstractParameter ap)
        This method computes the UnitDefinition that represents the unit of measurement of the given SBML Parameter and associates that unit with the given AbstractParameter.
        Parameters:
        p - A SBML Parameter in the SBML Model.
        ap - An AbstractParameter in the AbstractModel with the same identifier as p

      • computeParameterValue

        private void computeParameterValue(org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter p,
                                   AbstractParameter ap)
        This method computes an AbstractValue that represents the value of the given SBML Parameter in the SBML Model and associates that AbstractValue with the given AbstractParameter.
        Parameters:
        p - A SBML Parameter in the SBML Model.
        ap - An AbstractParameter in the AbstractModel that represents the given SBML Parameter.

      • generateParameters

        void generateParameters()
        This method generates all the AbstractParameters in the AbstractModel that represents the SBML Parameters in the SBML Model.
        After the call of this method, the AbstractParameters only contains informations about identifier, name and unit of measurement.

      • computeParametersValues

        void computeParametersValues()
        This method computes the AbstractValues that represent the values of the SBML Parameters in the SBML Model and associates them to the related AbstractParameters.
        That is, an AbstractValue av is associated with an AbstractParameter ap that has the same identifier as a SBML Parameter p whose the value is represented by av.
